<L>__{exterior street corner afternoon}
<A>__{here, at the same corner where she once waited for ron johnson, stacy waits for damone. cars pass, no damone.}
<L>__{interior hamilton house afternoon}
<A>__{stacy is on the phone, calling damone. we see the phone messages sheet that lists two calls for stacy, and none for brad. the line rings four times, then it's answered.}
<C>__{female voice}
<D>__{hello?}
<C>__{stacy}
<D>__{hello... is mike there?}
<C>__{female voice}
<D>__{hold on.}
<A>__{stacy sags, disbelieving, and looks at the clock on the kitchen wall. it's getting late...}
<C>__{female voice }
<D>__{he says he's helping his father in the garage and he'll call you back.}
<A>__{stacy is stunned.}
<C>__{female voice }
<D>__{hello?}
<A>__{stacy hangs up. she punches out another number, quickly.}
<C>__{mrs. barrett }
<D>__{hello?}
<C>__{stacy}
<D>__{hi, mrs. barrett. is linda there?}
<C>__{mrs. barrett }
<D>__{she went off to the beach. she'll be back later, though.}
<C>__{stacy}
<D>__{okay. thanks.}
<A>__{she looks at the clock again, then hears a noise in the driveway.}
<C>__{stacy }
<D>__{brad! hey, wait a second!}
<A>__{she runs out.}
